# TypeScript and React Best Practices

## TypeScript Guidelines
- Use strict TypeScript configuration
- Define all types explicitly, avoid `any`
- Use interfaces for object shapes, types for unions
- Export types from `types/index.ts` for reusability
- Use generic types when appropriate
- Leverage TypeScript's built-in utility types

## React Component Patterns
- Use functional components with hooks
- Define component props using interfaces
- Use React.FC only when necessary (children props)
- Prefer explicit return type annotations for complex components
- Use proper key props for lists
- Implement proper event handler typing

## Hooks Usage
- Use `useState` with proper type inference
- Use `useEffect` with proper dependency arrays
- Use `useMemo` and `useCallback` for performance optimization
- Custom hooks should start with `use` prefix
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks

## Form Handling
- Use controlled components for form inputs
- Implement proper form validation
- Use proper HTML form attributes (autocomplete, required, etc.)
- Handle form submission with proper error states
- Use proper input types (email, tel, password, etc.)

## Event Handling
- Use proper event types: `React.FormEvent`, `React.ChangeEvent`
- Use arrow functions for event handlers in JSX
- Prevent default behavior when needed
- Handle async operations in event handlers properly

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Use proper focus management
- Provide alt text for images
- Use proper heading hierarchy
